<p>In <a href="/wiki/Information_system" title="Information system" class="mw-redirect">information systems</a>, <b>identity management</b> is the management of the <a href="/wiki/Digital_identity" title="Digital identity">identity</a> <a href="/wiki/Life_cycle" title="Life cycle">life cycle</a> of entities (subjects or objects).</p>
<p>Identity management is <a href="/wiki/Multidisciplinary" title="Multidisciplinary" class="mw-redirect">multidisciplinary</a> covers many dimensions such as:</p>
<ul>
<li>technical. With <a href="/wiki/Identity_management_systems" title="Identity management systems">identity management systems</a>.</li>
<li>legal. Such as legistation for <a href="/wiki/Data_protection" title="Data protection" class="mw-redirect">data protection</a>.</li>
<li>police. For instance for dealing with <a href="/wiki/Identity_theft" title="Identity theft">identity theft</a>.</li>
<li>social and humanity. Dealing with issues such as <a href="/wiki/Privacy" title="Privacy">privacy</a>.</li>
<li>security. With elements such as access control.</li>
<li>organizations.</li>
</ul>
